The paper deals with graph sketches, which are a common topic in computer science theory. The focus is on distance preserving graph sketches, which are related to topics such as graph clustering and spanners. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are both likely categories. The paper also involves analyzing and improving upper bounds, which suggests that cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) may be relevant. Additionally, the paper applies distance preservers to graph clustering algorithms, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper involves constructing sparse subgraphs, which could be related to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
